               <p>I am wife to 
               <persName id="t17810530-33-person347">
                  Thomas
                   Townraw
               <interp inst="t17810530-33-person347" type="surname" value="Townraw"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-33-person347" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-33-person347" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The things mentioned in the indictment were all lost out of the back garret: my mother, 
               <persName id="t17810530-33-person348">
                  Mary
                   Gee
               <interp inst="t17810530-33-person348" type="surname" value="Gee"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-33-person348" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-33-person348" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , works in the back garret. On the 24th of May, about eight in the evening, I had just been across the way; coming up the steps of my own house, I met 
               <persName id="t17810530-33-person349">
                  Ann
                   Jones
               <interp inst="t17810530-33-person349" type="surname" value="Jones"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-33-person349" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-33-person349" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             coming out of the house. She asked if one Mrs. Connor lodged in my house, that took in men's clothes to scour. I said, No. She went on; I went in, and asked my mother, who was in the kitchen, if she had locked the garret door. She said, she had. I went up stairs directly, and found the door open: my husband's clothes were gone. I went down stairs, and made a hue and cry in the street: the prisoner was pursued, and taken.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17810530-33-person350">
                  BRYANT
                   CHANDLER
               <interp inst="t17810530-33-person350" type="surname" value="CHANDLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-33-person350" type="given" value="BRYANT"></interp>
